## New Features to Evaluate

### 🤖 AI-Powered Session Analysis

Use Amazon Bedrock (Claude) to automatically analyze session recordings for security threats:
- **SSH Sessions**: Detect privilege escalation, data exfiltration, credential access, suspicious commands
- **RDP Sessions** (future): OCR-based analysis for video recordings
- **Triggers**: Manual (on-demand button) + Automatic (during index rebuild)
- **Per-Tenant Config**: Enable/disable, model selection, auto-analyze SSH/RDP toggles
- **UI**: Threat level badges in session list, detailed findings on playback page
- **Storage**: New tables (`session_analysis`, `analysis_jobs`) for results and queue

**Status**: Planned · Spec: `docs/todo/ai-analysis.md`
**Priority**: ⭐⭐⭐ High · **Complexity**: High
**Value**: Security teams, compliance, incident response

---

### 📊 Audit Logging

Track who accessed which sessions and when - essential for compliance and forensics.
- Log session playback events (who, when, what session)
- Track search queries and filters used
- Export audit logs to CSV/JSON for compliance reports
- Store in `audit_logs` table with retention policy

**Priority**: ⭐⭐⭐ High · **Complexity**: Low-Medium
**Value**: Compliance requirement for many organizations

---

### 🔐 Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)

Currently all authenticated users see all sessions - add granular permissions.
- **Roles**: Admin, Auditor, Viewer (read-only)
- **Project-Level Access**: Users only see sessions from assigned projects
- **Server-Level Restrictions**: Limit access by server groups
- Store in `user_roles`, `role_permissions` tables

**Priority**: ⭐⭐⭐ High · **Complexity**: Medium-High
**Value**: Security requirement for multi-team deployments

---

### 🔖 Session Bookmarks & Flags

Allow users to mark sessions for follow-up or categorization.
- Bookmark sessions as "reviewed", "flagged for investigation", "important"
- Add notes/comments to bookmarked sessions
- Filter sessions by bookmark status
- Store in `session_bookmarks` table

**Priority**: ⭐⭐ Medium-High · **Complexity**: Low
**Value**: Improves investigation workflow

---

### 🔗 Session Sharing with Expiring Links

Generate time-limited shareable links for specific sessions.
- Expiring tokens (1 hour, 1 day, 1 week, custom)
- Optional PIN protection for shared links
- No authentication required (or PIN-only)
- Track share access in audit log

**Priority**: ⭐⭐ Medium · **Complexity**: Medium
**Value**: Collaboration, external auditor access

---

### 📤 Export Capabilities

Export search results and session data.
- **CSV Export**: Filtered session list with metadata
- **PDF Reports**: Session analysis results with findings
- **Bulk Download**: Multiple session files as .zip
- **Compliance Reports**: Pre-formatted for SOC2, ISO27001

**Priority**: ⭐⭐ Medium · **Complexity**: Low-Medium
**Value**: Reporting requirement for audits

---

### 🗄️ Retention Policies & Archival

Automatic cleanup of old sessions based on configurable policies.
- Per-tenant retention periods (30/60/90 days, 1 year, custom)
- Archive to S3 Glacier before deletion (cost optimization)
- Compliance with data retention regulations (GDPR, HIPAA)
- Dashboard showing storage costs and archival status

**Priority**: ⭐⭐ Medium · **Complexity**: Medium
**Value**: Cost optimization + compliance

---

### 🔔 Alerting & Notifications

Proactive notifications for security events.
- Email/Slack alerts for critical threat sessions (from AI analysis)
- Webhook integration for SIEM systems
- Configurable alert rules per tenant
- Alert on specific patterns (sudo commands, file access, etc.)

**Priority**: ⭐⭐ Medium-High · **Complexity**: Medium
**Value**: Proactive security monitoring

---

### 💬 Session Comments & Annotations

Investigation collaboration features.
- Add investigator comments to sessions
- Timeline of notes with timestamps
- Mention other users (@username)
- Searchable comment history

**Priority**: ⭐ Medium · **Complexity**: Low
**Value**: Team collaboration during investigations

---

### 📈 Advanced Analytics Dashboard

Enhanced statistics beyond current dashboard.
- User activity heatmaps (time of day, day of week)
- Server access frequency charts
- Top users by session count/duration
- Anomaly detection (unusual access patterns)
- Trend analysis (session volume over time)

**Priority**: ⭐ Low-Medium · **Complexity**: Low-Medium
**Value**: Security insights, capacity planning

---

### 🔄 Session Comparison (Diff View)

Compare two sessions side-by-side.
- Diff view for SSH commands (unified or split)
- Timeline synchronization for RDP videos
- Identify behavior changes between sessions
- Useful for detecting baseline deviations

**Priority**: ⭐ Low · **Complexity**: Medium-High
**Value**: Advanced investigation feature

---

### 🌐 REST API for External Integrations

Programmatic access for external tools and automation.
- `GET /api/v1/sessions` - List sessions with pagination
- `GET /api/v1/sessions/:id` - Get session details
- `GET /api/v1/sessions/:id/analysis` - Get AI analysis results
- `POST /api/v1/sessions/:id/bookmark` - Bookmark session
- API key authentication (separate from OIDC)
- Rate limiting per API key

**Priority**: ⭐⭐ Medium · **Complexity**: Low-Medium
**Value**: Automation, SIEM integration, custom dashboards

---

### 📺 Live Session Monitoring (Future)

Watch active sessions in real-time as they happen.
- WebSocket streaming from OPA gateway
- Real-time threat detection with AI
- Session interruption capability
- Requires gateway-level integration

**Priority**: ⭐ Low · **Complexity**: Very High
**Value**: Real-time security monitoring (major architectural change)

---

## Priority Legend

- ⭐⭐⭐ **High**: Should implement soon (compliance, security, core workflow)
- ⭐⭐ **Medium**: Valuable but not urgent (UX improvements, collaboration)
- ⭐ **Low**: Nice-to-have (advanced features, edge cases)